The key insight is that `Dsmooth` implies `isDiffeological`, which in turn implies `isContMDiffOn`. The proof uses the fact that `Dsmooth` maps are precisely the `isDiffeological` maps, which are defined to be `isContMDiffOn` with respect to the standard structure.

The proof is remarkably concise because the necessary lemmas (`isDiffeological.isContMDiffOn`) are already available in the library. The main work is done by these lemmas, which connect the different notions of smoothness.
